  "texts": [
    "This makes DRaFT-Q well-suited to low-budget deployments, while also offering better quality than fixed-rank LoRA and QLoRA baselines.",
    "Emerging Trends Across TasksAcross CommonsenseQA, OpenBookQA, GSM8K, OpenAssistant, OpenHermes, and UltraChat, we consistently observed that combining DRaFT-Q's two key innovations led to improved training stability and final performance.",
    "In OpenAssistant and OpenHermes, DRaFT-Q rapidly converged in under 1000 steps with LLaMA-2-7B, reaching final losses below 0.1.",
    "On UltraChat, LLaMA-2-13B trained to a stable final loss of 1.289 in just 800 steps, demonstrating DRaFT-Q's ability to scale while preserving convergence.",
    "We note that the slightly higher loss for LLaMA-2-13B is due to early stopping and adapter underfitting, as DRaFT-Q was trained for only 800 steps under hardware constraints."
  ],
